### POST /start - Send event with current timestamp
POST {{baseUrl}}/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "{{$guid}}",
  "timestamp": "{{$datetime iso8601}}",
  "type": "info",
  "message": "Event generated at {{$datetime iso8601}}"
}

### POST /start - Invalid request (missing fields)
POST {{baseUrl}}/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "",
  "timestamp": "2025-11-28T10:34:00Z",
  "type": "",
  "message": ""
}

### POST /start - Rapid fire events (run multiple times quickly)
POST {{baseUrl}}/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "rapid-{{$randomInt 1 1000}}",
  "timestamp": "{{$datetime iso8601}}",
  "type": "info",
  "message": "Rapid fire event #{{$randomInt 1 1000}}"
}
